                            <comment id="12758569" author="allee8285" created="Wed, 23 Sep 2009 04:50:24 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;The recent level spec has relaxed when the TransactionRequiredException will be thrown per the em interface contract.&lt;br/&gt;
-------------------------&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;@throws TransactionRequiredException if there is no transaction and if invoked on a container-managed EntityManager instance with PersistenceContextType.TRANSACTION&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;p&gt;&amp;gt;&amp;gt;&amp;gt;&amp;gt;  or with a lock mode other than NONE.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;public void refresh(Object entity, LockModeType lockMode);&lt;br/&gt;
-------------------------&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
